Reasoning: The paper discusses research on social network sites (SNSs) and their information, which falls under the category of social informatics (cs.SI). The paper also focuses on the issue of privacy in SNSs, which could fall under the categories of cybersecurity (cs.CY) and cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses the consequences of revealing personal information, which could fall under the category of social computing (cs.SOC). Finally, the paper discusses the applications of analyzing SNS information, which could fall under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
